createCampaign(bytes32,address).details: Initializes encrypted total to zero and sets up access permissions

donateZLETH(bytes32,bytes32,bytes).details: Requires prior ZLETH transfer to vault address via ZLETHWrapper.transfer()      Uses same encrypted input to add to campaign total without revealing amount      Separate transactions required due to FHE permission constraints with msg.sender

params.att: Attestation data for encrypted input verification

onClaimCallback(uint256,uint128,bytes[]).details: Protected by oracle-only access and KMS signature verification      Reduces encrypted campaign total by claimed amount (typically to zero)      Instructs wrapper to unwrap ZLETH and send ETH to creator

requestClaim(bytes32).details: Initiates public decryption process; oracle calls onClaimCallback with plaintext result      Only campaign creator can initiate claims

returns.requestId: Unique identifier for the decryption request

viewTotalHandle(bytes32).details: View function returns handle only, no FHE operations performed

returns._0: bytes32 handle for encrypted campaign total (for frontend userDecrypt)

_pendingClaim.details: Maps decryption requestId to campaignId for claim processing

decryptionOracle.details: Oracle address for public decryption operations

wrapper.details: ZLETHWrapper contract address for fund management

HandlesAlreadySavedForRequestID().notice: Returned if some handles were already saved for corresponding ID.

InvalidKMSSignatures().notice: Returned if the returned KMS signatures are not valid.

NoHandleFoundForRequestID().notice: Returned if there was not handle found for the requested ID.

UnsupportedHandleType().notice: Returned if the requested handle to be decrypted is not of a supported type.

DecryptionFulfilled(uint256).notice: This event is emitted when requested decryption has been fulfilled.

createCampaign(bytes32,address).notice: Creates a new campaign with unique ID and creator address

onClaimCallback(uint256,uint128,bytes[]).notice: Oracle callback: processes claim after decryption and instructs wrapper to send ETH

requestClaim(bytes32).notice: Creator requests claim: vault decrypts total and sends ETH via wrapper

viewTotalHandle(bytes32).notice: Returns encrypted total handle for a campaign
